VALUES (30, 'Eccentric Only Incline Push Up Video Exercise Guide', 'Chest', 'Strength', 'Bodyweight', 'Compound',
        'Push (Bilateral)', 'Beginner', 'Abs, Shoulders, Triceps', 'The eccentric only incline push up is an exercise used to strengthen the pushing muscles of the upper body.
One would typically perform the eccentric only incline push up as a way to progress to the point where they can perform traditional bodyweight push up variations.', 'Assume a tall kneeling position with your hands on a bench outside of shoulder width, toes tucked, and knees under hips.
