VALUES (70, 'Push Up to Side Plank Video Exercise Guide', 'Chest', 'Strength', 'Bodyweight', 'Compound',
        'Push (Bilateral)', 'Intermediate', 'Abs, Shoulders, Triceps', 'The push up to side plank is a combination exercise which combines the traditional push up with a side plank.
The primary muscle groups the push up to side plank will target are the muscles of the core and chest.
The push up portion of the push up to side plank will strengthen the muscles of chest, shoulders and tricep. The side plank portion will strengthen the muscles of the abdominals and obliques.', 'Assume a quadruped position on the floor with your hands under your shoulders, toes tucked, and knees under hips.
Extend one leg at a time and assume a pushup position with the legs straight, elbows extended, and head in a neutral position looking at the floor.
Slowly descend to the floor by retracting the shoulder blades and unlocking the elbows.
